  h2 Customize with Stylus
  p Customizing the block grid is easy with the Stylus variables provided in the
    span.class settings/block-grids.styl
    | file.
  h4 Stylus
  pre
    code(data-language="stylus")
      include css/gia.ui/_components/block-grids.settings.styl
  hr

  h2 Semantic Markup with Stylus Mixins
  p You apply block grid styles to semantic markup using Stylus mixins.
  h3 Basic
  p You can use the
    span.class create-block-grid()
    | mixin to create your own block grid, like so:
  .rw
    .cl.md-6
      h4 Stylus
      pre
        code(data-language="stylus").
          ul.custom-block-grid
            create-block-grid(20px, 3)
    .cl.md-6
      h4 HTML
      pre
        code(data-language="html").
          <ul class="custom-block-grid">
            <li><!-- Your content goest here --></li>
            <li><!-- Your content goest here --></li>
            <li><!-- Your content goest here --></li>
          </ul>
  h3 Advanced
  p You can further customize your block grid using the provided options in the
    span.class create-block-grid()
    | mixin:
  pre
    code(data-language="stylus").
      .custom-block-grid
        create-block-grid(
          // This controls how much space is between each item in the block grid. Use a variable or any pixel or em value
          space: block-grid-default-space,
          // This controls how many elements will be on each row of the block grid for small device
          small: 1,
          // This controls how many elements will be on each row of the block grid for medium device
          medium: 1,
          // This controls how many elements will be on each row of the block grid for large device
          large: 1
        )
  hr

  h3 Stylus Errors?
  p Make sure you import this line in main file:
  h4 Stylus
  pre
    code(data-language="css").
      @import '_components/block-grids'